{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug|type2=Poison}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Whirlipede}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=543|prev=Venipede|nextnum=545|next=Scolipede|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Whirlipede\n|jname=ホイーガ\n|jtranslit=Hoīga\n|tmname=Wheega\n|category=Curlipede\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Bug\n|type2=Poison\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Poison Point\n|ability2=Swarm\n|abilityd=Speed Boost\n|abilityold=Quick Feet\n|abilityoldcaption=Hidden Ability Gen. V{{tt|*|Will become Speed Boost when Whirlipede is transferred via Poké Transporter}}\n|ndex=544\n|udex=050\n|u2dex=044\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=121\n|height-ftin=3\'11"\n|height-m=1.2\n|weight-lbs=129.0\n|weight-kg=58.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|eggcycles=15\n|expyield=126\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|evtotal=2\n|evde=2\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Gray\n|catchrate=120\n|body=01\n|pokefordex=whirlipede\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Whirlipede\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ホイーガ\'\'\' \'\'Wheega\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Bug|Poison}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Venipede}} starting at [[level]] 22 and evolves into {{p|Scolipede}} starting at level 30.\n\n==Biology==\nWhirlipede is an insectoid Pokémon encased in a hard, segmented shell. It has two pairs of gray, horn-like feelers with dark gray stripes, with one pair extended upward from its front and the other pointing downward from its lower rear. Two poisonous barbs flank either side of each segment of its shell. The shell itself is gray, with red rings in the middle of each segment and a darker gray border circling its open center. Whirlipede\'s eyes can be seen within the center, and have slitted pupils, yellow sclerae, and thick, gray eyelids. Whirlipede remains motionless while storing energy for evolution, but will move to stab approaching predators with its poisonous spikes. If attacked, it can quickly spin its body like a wheel and crash furiously into opponents.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Burgh Whirlipede.png|thumb|left|250px|Whirlipede in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===In the main series===\n\n====Major appearances====\nWhirlipede debuted in \'\'[[BW023|Battling For The Love of Bug-Types!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Burgh]]. It battled against {{Ash}} during a [[Gym]] {{pkmn|battle}}, but was defeated by his newly evolved {{AP|Swadloon}}.\n\nA group of Whirlipede appeared in \'\'[[BW076|A Restoration Confrontation! Part 2]]\'\', where they attacked Ash, [[Ferris]], and a {{p|Tirtouga}} that Ferris had befriended.\n\nA Whirlipede appeared in \'\'[[BW119|Meowth, Colress and Team Rivalry!]]\'\'.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA Whirlipede appeared in \'\'[[M15|Kyurem VS. The Sword of Justice]]\'\' during the {{OBP|Swords of Justice|M15}} legend.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW023|Whirlipede|Ash\'s Pokédex|Whirlipede, the Curlipede Pokémon and the [[Evolution|evolved]] form of {{p|Venipede}}. Whirlipede can {{m|Steamroller|spin its hard shelled body like a tire to smash into opponents}}.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:Team Plasma Scolipede Whirlipede Sigilyph PG.png|thumb|250px|Whirlipede in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\nMultiple Whirlipede appeared in \'\'[[PG13|The Uprising]]\'\', under the ownership of some {{tc|Team Plasma Grunt}}s. They were used to battle [[Iris]] and the [[Unova]] [[Gym Leader]]s at [[N\'s Castle]].\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Burgh Whirlipede Adventures.png|thumb|125px|Whirlipede in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n[[Burgh]] has a Whirlipede which he used to battle [[Gorm]] in \'\'[[PS475|The Mystery of the Missing Fossil]]\'\'.\n\n[[Roxie]] has a Whirlipede that first appeared in \'\'[[PS535|Angry Boy]]\'\'. She used it to battle against a group of {{tc|Team Plasma Grunt}}s at [[Castelia Sewers]].\n\nA {{tc|Team Plasma Grunt}}\'s Whirlipede was seen in [[PS545]].\n{{-}}\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Whirlipede (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Bug|type2=Poison}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=050|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=044|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=Storing energy for evolution, it sits. But, when predators approach, it moves to stab them with poison spikes.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=121|label1=Central|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=Bug|type2=Poison}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=V}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|area=[[Pinwheel Forest]] (inner) ({{DL|Tall grass|dark grass}})}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|area=[[Pinwheel Forest]] (inner)<br>[[Lostlorn Forest]] ({{DL|Tall grass|dark grass}})}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=X|v2=Y|t=FFF|area=[[Frie